genet 65 1170 1177 1999 retrovar retrovar computes the asymptotically correct variances for the estimates of the parameters from a logistic regression done with data which have been ascertained retrospectively and have certain covariance structures see logistic regression of family data from retrospective study designs as whittemore and j halpern genetic epidemiology 25 177 189 2003 weightedkac weightedkac description to be supplied soon you are here stanford medicine school of medicine departments health research and policy epidemiology navigation for this section epidemiology overview degree program courses epidemiology research seminar seminars statistical software jobs opportunity site navigation home people overview faculty profiles courtesy faculty consulting & visiting faculty emeriti senior research scientists lecturers hrp telephonedirectory education overview computer resources centers and labs research overview data coordinating center dcc patient care overview community overview newsletter make a gift divisions overview biostatistics overview courses workshops bmt biostatistics seminars biostatistics group wiki epidemiology overview degree program courses epidemiology research seminar seminars statistical software health services research overview rip research in progress seminar seminars masters degree program contact us department contacts job openings stanford medicine resources stanford medicine getting care overview find a physician find a clinical care center stanford hospital & clinics lucile packard children's hospital emergency research overview school of medicine news & resources clinical trials departments institutes & centers faculty profiles education & training overview school of medicine programs admissions continuing medical education alumni lane medical library community overview stanford health library community newsletter volunteering public service & community partnerships renewal & new building projects about us overview news careers